{"title":"Trek Emonda ALR alloy road bike now looks like it’s carbon","link":"https://bikerumor.com/trek-emonda-alr-alloy-road-bike-now-looks-like-its-carbon/","date":1682013600000,"content":"<p>The new Trek Emonda ALR brings sleek, carbon-like looks and a very lightweight frame to crit racers looking for a top-level frame on (a bit of) a budget. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>Kamm Tail aero shaping and integrated internal cable routing make it more aero. Geometry is racier, too, and tire clearance opens up to modern standards.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/2023-Trek-Emonda-ALR5-5.jpg\"><img width=\"800\" height=\"534\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/2023-Trek-Emonda-ALR5-5-800x534.jpg\" alt=\"closeup details of new trek emonda ALR\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/2023-Trek-Emonda-ALR5-5-800x534.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/2023-Trek-Emonda-ALR5-5-297x198.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/2023-Trek-Emonda-ALR5-5-120x80.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/2023-Trek-Emonda-ALR5-5-768x512.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/2023-Trek-Emonda-ALR5-5-1536x1025.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/2023-Trek-Emonda-ALR5-5-720x480.jpg 720w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/2023-Trek-Emonda-ALR5-5.jpg 2000w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Using heavily shaped tubes with smoothed welds, the frame looks very much like it has carbon tubes, especially at the headtube.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/2023-Trek-Emonda-ALR5-6.jpg\"><img width=\"800\" height=\"534\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/2023-Trek-Emonda-ALR5-6-800x534.jpg\" alt=\"closeup details of new trek emonda ALR\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/2023-Trek-Emonda-ALR5-6-800x534.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/2023-Trek-Emonda-ALR5-6-297x198.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/2023-Trek-Emonda-ALR5-6-120x80.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/2023-Trek-Emonda-ALR5-6-768x512.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/2023-Trek-Emonda-ALR5-6-1536x1025.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/2023-Trek-Emonda-ALR5-6-720x480.jpg 720w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/2023-Trek-Emonda-ALR5-6.jpg 2000w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>A larger head tube makes room for internal routing running into the headset, making it compatible with <em>some</em> quasi-integrated cockpits, but not Madone’s SLR one-piece bar/stem because of it’s non-round base shape. But kits from FSA, Deda, etc., should work.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/2023-Trek-Emonda-ALR5-3.jpg\"><img width=\"800\" height=\"600\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/2023-Trek-Emonda-ALR5-3-800x600.jpg\" alt=\"closeup details of new trek emonda ALR\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/2023-Trek-Emonda-ALR5-3-800x600.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/2023-Trek-Emonda-ALR5-3-297x223.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/2023-Trek-Emonda-ALR5-3-120x90.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/2023-Trek-Emonda-ALR5-3-768x576.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/2023-Trek-Emonda-ALR5-3-1536x1152.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/2023-Trek-Emonda-ALR5-3.jpg 2000w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Tire clearance increases to 700×28, and wheels come tubeless ready, but complete bikes come with tubes and tube-type tires.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/2023-Trek-Emonda-ALR5-1.jpg\"><img width=\"800\" height=\"600\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/2023-Trek-Emonda-ALR5-1-800x600.jpg\" alt=\"closeup details of new trek emonda ALR\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/2023-Trek-Emonda-ALR5-1-800x600.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/2023-Trek-Emonda-ALR5-1-297x223.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/2023-Trek-Emonda-ALR5-1-120x90.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/2023-Trek-Emonda-ALR5-1-768x576.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/2023-Trek-Emonda-ALR5-1-1536x1152.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/2023-Trek-Emonda-ALR5-1.jpg 2000w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The new Emonda ALR upgrades to a threaded T47 BB, so no more pressfit. The frame is mechanical group compatible, with a few limitations on front derailleurs…those need to have integrated cable stops, or you can add an adapter to work with some SRAM and older Shimano front mechs.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/2023-Trek-Emonda-ALR5-4.jpg\"><img width=\"800\" height=\"534\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/2023-Trek-Emonda-ALR5-4-800x534.jpg\" alt=\"closeup details of new trek emonda ALR\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/2023-Trek-Emonda-ALR5-4-800x534.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/2023-Trek-Emonda-ALR5-4-297x198.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/2023-Trek-Emonda-ALR5-4-120x80.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/2023-Trek-Emonda-ALR5-4-768x512.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/2023-Trek-Emonda-ALR5-4-1536x1025.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/2023-Trek-Emonda-ALR5-4-720x480.jpg 720w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/2023-Trek-Emonda-ALR5-4.jpg 2000w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Frame weight is a claimed 1,257g painted, and fork is 406g. Complete bikes are 19.41lb (8.8kg) for the ALR6, which won’t be available in North America. The ALR5, with Shimano 105 R7000 mechanical, will come in black and the blue/pink/red fade shown here for $2,299 with a claimed weight of 19.85lb (9.0kg).</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/2023-Trek-Emonda-ALR6.jpg\"><img width=\"800\" height=\"600\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/2023-Trek-Emonda-ALR6-800x600.jpg\" alt=\"2023 trek emonda ALR aluminum road bike with shaped tubes that look like carbon\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/2023-Trek-Emonda-ALR6-800x600.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/2023-Trek-Emonda-ALR6-297x223.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/2023-Trek-Emonda-ALR6-120x90.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/2023-Trek-Emonda-ALR6-768x576.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/2023-Trek-Emonda-ALR6-1536x1152.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/2023-Trek-Emonda-ALR6.jpg 2000w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/2023-trek-emonda-ALR-geometry-chart.jpg\"><img width=\"800\" height=\"663\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/2023-trek-emonda-ALR-geometry-chart-800x663.jpg\" alt=\"trek emonda ALR geometry chart\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/2023-trek-emonda-ALR-geometry-chart-800x663.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/2023-trek-emonda-ALR-geometry-chart-297x246.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/2023-trek-emonda-ALR-geometry-chart-120x99.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/2023-trek-emonda-ALR-geometry-chart-768x636.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/2023-trek-emonda-ALR-geometry-chart.jpg 1340w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The bike comes in an impressive eight frame sizes, ranging from 47 to 62.</p>\n\n\n\n<p><em><a href=\"https://www.trekbikes.com\" target=\"_blank\">TrekBikes.com</a></em></p>\n<p>The post <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/trek-emonda-alr-alloy-road-bike-now-looks-like-its-carbon/\">Trek Emonda ALR alloy road bike now looks like it’s carbon</a> appeared first on <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com\">Bikerumor</a>.</p>","author":"Tyler Benedict","siteTitle":"Bikerumor","siteHash":"49f427af0a926f4232eb837006841d7242e153e3afbb590f32e4b104ea3e2718","entryHash":"9da060f402bf6f1cd6b63ffde99951495d1bce10c5e07ddb1e579c17b1ec9f76","category":"Cycling"}